[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":390},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F03\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F03\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F03\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F03\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc\u002F":365,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2020\u002F02\u002F03\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc\u002F":374},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20200203\u002F3949702627\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":52,"date":346,"description":347,"extension":348,"lang":349,"meta":350,"navigation":351,"path":352,"readingMinutes":353,"seo":354,"standalone":355,"stem":356,"tags":357,"tldr":362,"updated":346,"url":363,"__hash__":364},"content\u002Fen\u002FJavaScript\u002Fpixijs-v5-00-intro-and-toc.md","PixiJS V5 Tutorial (0) - Why I'm Doing This + Full Table of Contents","1001694669",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":337},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,27,30,33,36,40,43,56,59,62,66,76,325,329],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"This series is basically something I'm writing for the w3HexSchool Year-of-the-Rat full marathon ironman challenge run by HexSchool. For this first post, let me talk a bit about why I picked PixiJS.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"why-pixijs","Why PixiJS?",[17,25,26],{},"The main reason is that on one project I had to build a bunch of effects, and one section in particular had to use PixiJS. Since I didn't really understand the tech, I figured I'd just throw myself in the deep end during this challenge and force myself to learn it. My hope is that by the end I can at least reach the \"ohh, okay\" level — where I can read PixiJS source code and actually follow what's going on.",[17,28,29],{},"The other reason is I'm honestly pretty curious about the kind of effects PixiJS can produce. A lot of games are made with PixiJS too. And because I'd already poked at it a little during that project, I was even able to tweak some of the code in there. So... I figured I'd just give writing about it a shot.",[17,31,32],{},"I'm hoping I can fully complete all 40 weeks of the challenge and walk away with the Golden Horn Award (an actual physical trophy)!!!!!!",[17,34,35],{},"Either way, the end goal is the Golden Horn Award. (Here I come!)",[12,37,39],{"id":38},"before-you-start","Before You Start",[17,41,42],{},"For this series I'd recommend you already have a basic grasp of the following:",[44,45,46,50,53],"ul",{},[47,48,49],"li",{},"CSS & HTML",[47,51,52],{},"JavaScript",[47,54,55],{},"Canvas (if you've touched it at all, you'll have an easier time — but it's not required, since I came in without ever having used it.)",[17,57,58],{},"If you've got those down, I think you should be able to follow this series fine, because I also came in having never touched PixiJS and just researched everything online myself. Unless I write it really badly (which, I'll admit, I probably will).",[17,60,61],{},"But if you've already learned Canvas, then I think this'll feel really natural to you, because PixiJS itself is built on top of Canvas.",[12,63,65],{"id":64},"table-of-contents","Table of Contents",[67,68,69],"blockquote",{},[17,70,71,75],{},[72,73,74],"strong",{},"Note","\nThis section will keep getting updated.",[44,77,78,85,91,97,103,109,115,121,127,133,139,145,151,157,163,169,175,181,187,193,199,205,211,217,223,229,235,241,247,253,259,265,271,277,283,289,295,301,307,313,319],{},[47,79,80,84],{},[81,82,83],"a",{"href":3},"PixiJS V5 Tutorial (0) - Intro & Table of Contents"," (article in Mandarin)",[47,86,87,84],{},[81,88,90],{"href":89},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20200210\u002F3949702627\u002F","PixiJS V5 Tutorial (1) - Setting Up PixiJS",[47,92,93,84],{},[81,94,96],{"href":95},"\u002Fjavascript\u002F20200217\u002F4014508881\u002F","PixiJS V5 Tutorial (2) - WebGL and Rend